cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.DS 

The paper deals with the dynamic behavior of network creation games, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and network science (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the decentralized creation of overlay networks (cs.DC) and the use of distributed algorithms (cs.SI) for finding equilibrium networks. Finally, the paper presents empirical simulations (cs.DS) to contrast the negative theoretical results.
